 LAGOS State Government said it will close the PWD level crossing from Sunday to Tuesday, March 17 for the laying of track along the level crossing on Ikeja axis. A statement from the Ministry of Transportation said the routes will be closed daily from 6pm to 6am, adding that alternative routes have been provided for road users. The statement said motorists plying PWD level crossing will be diverted to Ashade Underpass, by Idi Mongoro, to join Ikeja Along or climb Airport Bridge, by Ikeja General Hospital, to link Oshodi Motorway.